<TITLE> Bangladesh ambassador to France Ruhul Amin dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh ambassador to France Ruhul Amin died in hospital after he suffered a brain haemorrhage, a foreign ministry official said Thursday. Amin was 48. Updates with condolences "He (Amin) has expired," Samina Naz, a director for the foreign affairs adviser's office, told bdnews24.com Thursday night. Earlier, Nazmul Quaunine, director general of the external publicity wing at the foreign affairs ministry, had told bdnews24.com: "He (Amin) is on the life support system. We have the updates until 5pm (Bangladesh time)." Doctors have sought permission from the family to take him off the life support system, but no decision could be made as none of the family was around at the time. Amin suffered a brain haemorrhage Wednesday midnight (Bangladesh time) and was rushed to a clinic in Paris where doctors suggested transfer to another hospital for better treatment. Foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury expressed condolences to Amin's family. Amin was appointed to France as ambassador in June 2007. Prior to his job in Paris, Amin, a 1984 batch career diplomat, was posted in Bahrain as Bangladesh envoy. bdnews24.com/k
